88fc-49a81c5fd243?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ec=
HmePkbA3ys ].)
Mike Tyson, Sugarcubes and Snow White: Understanding Rosal=C3=ADa=E2=80=99s=
 Berghain [ https://substack.com/redirect/7860ba50-42f7-4a15-98f9-b69a5c7bc=
a32?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ]
=E2=80=94Tara Maria Gonzalez  in Cult Classic =20
At the beginning of Berghain, we see Rosal=C3=ADa come home from what we ca=
n presume is a late night out. The curtains in her house are shut and when =
she thrusts them open, light streams through the apartment, suggesting she =
left at night and is returning as the sun is rising. An orchestra appears b=
ehind her, blaring violins and clarinets, as she sits down to dip a sugar c=
ube contemplatively into a cup of coffee.
The sugar cube moment is a direct reference to Krzysztof Kie=C5=9Blowski=E2=
=80=99s Three Colours: Blue (1993). The psychological drama is part of a tr=
ilogy about the French revolutionary ideas of liberty, equality and fratern=
ity. Each film features a different color from the French flag; this film o=
bviously represents blue. Kie=C5=9Blowski has said that the film is about =
=E2=80=9Cemotional liberty.=E2=80=9D
Three Colours: Blue is about a woman named Julie who loses her famous compo=
ser husband and five-year-old daughter in a car crash. The way that she dec=
ides to handle this grief is by not handling it at all. She removes herself=
 from anything that reminds her or ties her to them. She sells all of their=
 belongings, gets rid of sheets of incomplete music and moves out of the la=
rge country home they all shared and into an apartment on her own in Paris.
And while she can escape the physical items that remind her of them, she ca=
nnot rid herself of their memories. She cannot get that emotional liberty. =
They still exist in her. And whenever she thinks of her husband or her daug=
hter or is reminded of them subconsciously or against her will, the score o=
f her husband=E2=80=99s music suddenly plays over the entire scene. It haun=
ts her. They haunt her.
You don=E2=80=99t see the orchestra but you hear them, which clearly inspir=
ed the part of the music video where the orchestra is following Rosalia eve=
rywhere. They represent her intrusive thoughts, which we also know from the=
 CentsdeCels shirt she wore in the teaser for the music video that read: =
=E2=80=9CMy intrusive thoughts sound like this.=E2=80=9D
